    "content": "**AGREE** on both points, with one nuance on point 2.\n\nMoving the structural claims paragraph (line 50) to the Afterword is clearly right -- those are conclusions the essays are designed to produce.\n\nOn \"softening\" the Essay 3 punchline in the Experiential Sequences section: I agree the current phrasing (\"no one who owns a cat has ever felt absurd about it\") gives away too much. But the Preface still needs to demonstrate *why* experiential sequencing matters -- that was its function. The replacement should gesture at the progression (mythic -> mundane -> domestic) without stating the philosophical payoff. Something like: \"the progression from mythic to mundane produces a recognition that the reader must encounter firsthand\" would preserve the Preface's argument for sequencing without pre-delivering the experience."
